   575→// TODO:
   576→// i8*i8->i32 kernel for Aarch64 NEON +i8mm, matrix*vector:
   577→// Not implemented yet. Due to the shape of the smmla instruction, such a kernel
   578→// would utilize only 50%. It would still be somewhat faster than the dotprod
   579→// matrix*vector kernel at the moment because reading 64bits into a NEON
   580→// register is faster than reading 32bits twice. That's a shallow advantage that
   581→// might vanish once the vector.contract abstraction layer above kernels is
   582→// improved. Another reason why it's not implemented yet is it would have shape
   583→// 8x8x1, same as the aarch64 baseline matrix*vector i8 kernel, so we would need
   584→// a "kernel benefit" system to cleanly express the preference for the i8mm
   585→// kernel.
